<div id="review_13482035" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/13482035" />
    <a title="Annie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/389577-annie"><img alt="Annie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1190099510p2/389577.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/13482035?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annie" href="/user/show/389577-annie">Annie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13482035" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6897675739840092320">I read this book in prepartion to our trip to Cambodia in April. I would have read it anyway, however, because I love depressing autobiographies. This one was far different than any other I have ever read being that it was from a child&apos;s perspective. It retold her unbelievable story of escaping the killing fields during Pol Pot&apos;s reign with the Khmer Rouge. I think everyone in my generation needs to read this book. Many people my age do not even know Pol Pot&apos;s name, moreless that he killed over </span>
  <span id="freeText6897675739840092320" style="display:none">I read this book in prepartion to our trip to Cambodia in April. I would have read it anyway, however, because I love depressing autobiographies. This one was far different than any other I have ever read being that it was from a child's perspective. It retold her unbelievable story of escaping the killing fields during Pol Pot's reign with the Khmer Rouge. I think everyone in my generation needs to read this book. Many people my age do not even know Pol Pot's name, moreless that he killed over 2 million people...in the 1970's none the less! Her story will make you appreciate even the simplest things in life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6897675739840092320" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
