<div id="review_4517713247" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4517713247" />
    <a title="saïd" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27143253-sa-d"><img alt="saïd" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576544217p2/27143253.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4517713247?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="saïd" class="user" itemprop="url" name="saïd" href="/user/show/27143253-sa-d">saïd</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27143253-sa-d?shelf=viet-cetera">viet-cetera</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27143253-sa-d?shelf=2_nonfiction">2_nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4517713247" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1898579763326784942">This is not really a well-written book. The prose isn&apos;t great; the pacing is all over the place. It&apos;s been criticised for major historical inaccuracies. But it&apos;s also told from the perspective of a child (Loung Ung was ten years old when she fled Cambodia), and is one of many perspectives on the horrors of the Khmer Rouge.<br/><br/>In this case I think the film adaptation, <u>មុនដំបូងខ្មែរក្រហមសម្លាប់ប៉ារបស់ខ្ញុំ</u> (2017), far outstrips the original work. The film was directed by Angelina Jolie, who has dual A</span>
  <span id="freeText1898579763326784942" style="display:none">This is not really a well-written book. The prose isn't great; the pacing is all over the place. It's been criticised for major historical inaccuracies. But it's also told from the perspective of a child (Loung Ung was ten years old when she fled Cambodia), and is one of many perspectives on the horrors of the Khmer Rouge.<br /><br />In this case I think the film adaptation, <u>មុនដំបូងខ្មែរក្រហមសម្លាប់ប៉ារបស់ខ្ញុំ</u> (2017), far outstrips the original work. The film was directed by Angelina Jolie, who has dual American-Cambodian citizenship, and co-written by Jolie and Ung; the majority of the film is in Khmer, with only a small amount in French and English (and Vietnamese). It was a masterfully constructed film, and I'd recommend that anyone interested in learning about Ung's story to watch the film rather than to read the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1898579763326784942" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


